{"id":"1605.07997","submitter":"Arseniy Akopyan","authors":"Arseniy Akopyan, Vladislav Vysotsky","title":"On the Lengths of Curves Passing through Boundary Points of a Planar\n  Convex Shape","comments":"7 pages, 8 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.MG","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We study the lengths of curves passing through a fixed number of points on\nthe boundary of a convex shape in the plane. We show that for any convex shape\n$K$, there exist four points on the boundary of $K$ such that the length of any\ncurve passing through these points is at least half of the perimeter of $K$. It\nis also shown that the same statement does not remain valid with the additional\nconstraint that the points are extreme points of $K$. Moreover, the factor\n$\\frac12$ cannot be achieved with any fixed number of extreme points. We\nconclude the paper with few other inequalities related to the perimeter of a\nconvex shape.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 May 2016 18:31:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 6 Sep 2016 17:54:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-07"}
