th vanishing amplitude $V$. At\nsmall but finite amplitude $V$, the hexagonal phase is distorted and\nhexatically locked at an angle of $\\varphi \\approx 3.8^\\circ$ with respect to\nthe substrate lattice. The square-to-hexagonal transformation in this\ntwo-dimensional commensurate-incommensurate system thus involves a complex\npathway with various non-trivial lattice- and modulated phases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 May 2016 13:19:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-24"}
