ays; fortunately the shift in $\\kappa$ only induces\na 0.9 (0.4) percent bias on $H_0$ for quads (doubles). We therefore conclude\nthat whilst the properties of typical quasar lenses and their lines-of-sight do\ndeviate from the global population, the total magnitude of this effect is\nlikely a subdominant effect for current analyses, but has the potential to be a\nmajor systematic for samples of $\\sim$25 or more lenses.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 May 2016 15:50:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-07"}
